A Red Carpet Mystery, Hollywood Ratings
Secrets, Trump=E2=80=99s Disassociated Press
---------------------------------------

Happy Friday and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your digital
capsule of Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni examines the existential tumult plaguing Jim M=
oore=E2=80=99s Village Roadshow, the once high-flying film finance company =
now teetering on the edge of collapse. With a crippling legal fight against=
 Warner Bros., private equity overlords, and industry-wide instability, can=
 it ever regain its stature as a Hollywood
powerhouse?

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Dylan Byers points his Geiger counter at the latest f=
allout emanating from Jeff Bezos=E2=80=99s Washington Post. John Ourand rev=
eals ESPN=E2=80=99s potential scheme to keep baseball on TV. And exclusivel=
y for Inner Circle members, Lauren Sherman digs into a pair of red carpet p=
lotlines: the tenuous return of
Georgina Chapman=E2=80=99s Marchesa and the Hollywood anointment of Saint L=
aurent Productions.

Meanwhile, on the pods: Matt and Nielsen=E2=80=99s Brian Fuhrer demystify h=
ow ratings actually work in 2025. On Fashion People, Lauren connects with T=
